info.senderName: NWS Cheyenne (Southeastern Wyoming and Western Nebraska)
info.headline: High Wind Warning issued November 15 at 2:08AM MST until November 17 at 8:00AM MST by NWS Cheyenne
info.description: ...HIGH WIND WARNING IN EFFECT FROM 8 PM THIS EVENING TO 8 AM MST FRIDAY... * WHAT...West winds 30 to 45 mph with gusts up to 70 mph expected. * WHERE...North Snowy Range Foothills including the Arlington and Elk Mountain areas along Interstate 80. * WHEN...From 8 PM this evening to 8 AM MST Friday. * IMPACTS...Mainly to transportation. Strong cross winds will be hazardous to light weight or high profile vehicles, including campers and tractor trailers.
info.instruction: A High Wind Warning means a hazardous high wind event is expected or occurring. Sustained wind speeds of at least 40 mph or gusts of 58 mph or more can lead to property damage.
